State hereinafter expressed, does hereby agree to furnish to the State services and materials, as follows:
(Set forth service to be rendered by Contractor, amount to be paid Contractor, time for performance or completion, and attach plans and specifications, if any.)
The attached project titled "Iron Supplementation of Milk, " marked Exhibit A,
submitted to Dairy Council of California, is hereby made a part of this agreement
Said project will be completed not later than June 30, 1976.And
The total amount to be paid by the Dairy Council of California to Contractor
under the terms of this agreement shall not exceed $4,026, payable as follows:
$2,026 upon approval of this agreement by the Director of Food and Agriculture,
$1,000 on or about January 1, 1976, and $1, 000 upon completion of the project.
Any item of inventoriable equipment which is purchased at a cost of $1, 000 or
more with funds paid by the State pursuant to this contract shall be the
property of the State for three years following date of purchase. Immediately
upon assuming custody of such equipment, contractor agrees to execute an
"Equipment Loan Agreement Form" or similar instrument evidenceing its possession
of the equipment, and to return not less than two copies of said form or other
The provisions on the reverse side hereof constitute a part of this agreement. ":
